ANN7 sources can now reveal additional names of people who were potential targets for assassination by the Anti-State Capture Death Squad Alliance.The list includes cabinet ministers such namely State Security minister David Mahlobo, Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs minister Des Van Rooyen and Mineral Resources minister Mosebenzi Zwane.The hit list also includes the names of ANC Youth League president Collen Maine, Umkhonto we Sizwe Military Veterans Association chairperson Kebby Maphatsoe, National Prosecuting Authority head Shaun Abrahams, Free State Premier Ace Magashule, SAA board chairperson Dudu Myeni, Fana Hlongwane.On Thursday ANN7 sources revealed that President Jacob Zuma&#8217;s name alongside that of former Eskom CEO and member of parliament Brian Molefe, Eskom board chairman Ben Ngubane and all the Gupta brothers appeared on the hit list.The revelation of the hit list comes as the suspected mastermind behind the plot Elvis Ramosebudi (33) made a brief first appearance in the Johannesburg Magistrate Court after he was arrested by the Hawks in Midrand, Johannesburg on Wednesday.Ramosebudi is believed to be the leader of two organisations, the Anti-State Capture Death Squad Alliance and the Anti-White Monopoly Capitalist Regime which are alleged to be behind a plot to assassinate South Africans who were implicated in former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela s State capture report.On Friday Ramosebudi&#8217;s mental health was called into question after the state called for him to be referred for mental observation.State prosecutor King Masemola the accused plot masterminds actions, particularly, approaching listed companies asking for money to commit a crime, using one s personal details was not normal.The matter was postponed until 2 May to give Ramosebudi an opportunity to meet with his legal aid lawyer and allow for further investigation.He faces charges of conspiracy to commit murder.-TNA Reporter